description: At Wimbledon , home of tennis , Dee and Kelly seek a mysterious talisman, Tower and Brody chase Dee and Kelly , Martin and Java are investigating an invincible player and Angie , as usual , finds herself in the middle without understanding anything!
name: Complotto a Wimbledon

description:
Journey back to the days of drive-ins and hula hoops and join Archie and his teenage friends as they frolic through the frantic Fifties!

Archie Americana Series Best of the Fifties is a trade paperback collection of Archie comic stories from 1950 to 1959.
name: Best of the Fifties

description: Archie Americana Series Best of the Sixties is a trade paperback collection of Archie comics stories from 1960 to 1969.
name: Best of the Sixties

description: Superman's power fluctuations are out of control, and while he's battling everyone around him in a mass of confusion, a surprising figure tries to intervene! But can anyone ‚Äì or anything ‚Äì stop an enraged Kryptonian?
name: Enemies

description:
Another Cold Day Part 4

After the disastrous confrontation between Brimstone, Mr. Hostile & the NYPD led by Detective Altar; New York City is in chaos! The long-thought-executed serial killer Mr. Hostile is on the loose, Brimstone has been captured by the NYPD and Detective Altar, once again, mysteriously survives almost certain death! Now all the pieces come together in this stunning climax to the conclusion of the story that marks the beginning of the Brimstone saga...
name: Brimstone and The Borderhounds: Another Cold Day Part Four

description:
Graphic novel adaptation of the following classic Lovecraft tales:

The Stranger

The Music of Erich Zahn

Nyarlathotep

The Nameless City

The Temple
name: The Temple

description:
Hughie's return to the fold is not all he'd hoped for, with our hero managing to incur the displeasure of everyone else on the team. At least he still has Annie, but her patience is growing somewhat limited. Meanwhile, the investigation into Jack from Jupiter continues- with Butcher growing more and more suspicious about what he finds...

Note: The Legend is only seen in pictures and a written transcript of a conversation he had years ago.
name: The Big Ride, Part Two

description: In the bombastic finale to this 4-part series, the Suicide Girls have to take down Way of Life, find Xenia, and rescue the other kidnapped SG's. Can Sana trust Frank, or is she the traitor in their midst?
name: 4 (of 4)

description: Batman's slipperiest foe steps out of the shadows and into the spotlight for a "Legends of the Dark Knight" issue that reveals, for the first time, the full story of Inque! Her past is blacker than anyone ever knew... and considering the new ally she's fallen in with, her future could be darker still!
name: Legends of the Dark Knight: Inque

description: Martin , Java and Altrove are on the footsteps of a legendary machine that cancels bad luck , hoping to avoid the catastrophic effects of an evil comet.
name: L'anno della cometa

description: While the core team takes a scant few minutes to recuperate from their encounter with the Juggernaut, Fixer readies the B-team to reinforce them in Chicago just in time for a new WMD from Sin to touch down and unleash a horde of monsters. The tech for which is stolen from Baron Zemo, and he isn't at all pleased...
name: A New WMD

description: Year 2026. Altrove built a time machine , but Dee and Kelly try to steal it for their criminal purposes . In 2006, however , something had happened that had brought Diana and Angie in a distant future, grappling with the Chronopolice who had vanished the research of Altrove about time travel .
name: Oggi, domani e ieri

description:
Frank Castle's back in the game, but how does a cop describe his brush with him?

TIME TO GET BACK TO WORK. For Frank Castle death comes easy...life is where things gets complicated. Fully loaded with the Eisner winning writer Greg Rucka (Batwoman, Queen and Country, WOLVERINE) and neo-superstar artist Marco Checchetto (Amazing Spider-Man, Daredevil), the BIGGEST GUN of all returns with blood on his hands and vengeance in his eyes. As New York City's body counts continue to rise, the city's streets are teeming with more methodical criminals than ever and a police force doing it's best to keep its head above water. The Punisher has returned to serve his own brand of justice with everything's he's got... but can he survive the darkness stored in his own arsenal? Plus bonus pages exploring some of the new personalities in Frank's life...and how closely intertwined living is with dying.
name: Punisher: One

description: With Brooklyn held within the grip of chaos, Hercules and his unlikely band of allies make their final push for freeing Brooklyn from the grip of Kyknos and his Warhawks...
name: Black Rapture

description: While Red Hulk is flying cross country due to the possessed Thing's powerhouse assault, his foes M.O.D.O.K and Zero/One team up to combat the Invading Nazi hordes (they can't let somebody ELSE sieze control, after all).
name: Planet of Fear, Pt. 2

description: This is a double issue and features both #15-2011 and #16-2011.

Signs continue to appear throughout the Multiverse that the Cosmic Balance is in peril, and the Eternal Champion is caught in the crosshairs! Across worlds, Elric, Hawkmoon and Corum begin to face the force that threatens to overpower them all, while Eric Beck, a modern-day video game designer, must acknowledge that his reoccurring dreams of a Pale Prince aren't all in his head.

All hell's breakin' loose in Times Square! Butcher Baker vs. three villainous m**therf**kers! Even the military gets in on the fun! Face it, this issue has all the hallmarks of a classic - tons of s**t blows up real good! What more could anyone ask for in their supersexploitation comicbook?

Foghorn J., I say, Foghorn J. Leghorn is at it again! Whether it's antagonizing The Barnyard Dawg or babysitting Miss Prissy's son, ol' Foggy is mixing it up as your favorite cocky, blustering, know-it-all rooster. Join us in celebrating the wisecracks and unwise antics of our favorite ranch-bound sage! (That's a joke, I say, that's a joke, son.)
name: Merit Badgering
